==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frugality
<hw>Fru*gal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Frugalities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>frugalitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>frugalit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality of being frugal; prudent economy; that
careful management of anything valuable which expends nothing
unnecessarily, and applies what is used to a profitable purpose; thrift;
--- opposed to <xex>extravagance</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Frugality</qex> is founded on the principle that all riches
have⟦br⟧
limits.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A sparing use; sparingness; <as>as, frugality of
praise</as>.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Economy; parsimony. See
<er>Economy</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frugally</ent>⟦br⟧
